overview: Arjun and Anu are fraternal twins who manage to run a scam in the US from India via a call center. With police officer Kumar hot on their heels, will they manage to escape the system?

overview: Amma Rajyam Lo Kadapa Biddalu (Kadapa Children in Mother's Kingdom) is a political satire film directed by Ram Gopal Varma and Siddartha Thatolu. It explores caste, dynasties, religion and their influence on politics in Andhra Pradesh, India.
title: Amma Rajyam Lo Kadapa Biddalu

overview: A young man faces immense pressure from his family to move to America, get a job and have his life settled abroad.
title: Pressure Cooker

overview: After his family is murdered by former foes, an IPS officer and his daughter fake their deaths. Trouble ensues when the enemies discover their survival, prompting the officer to confront them to safeguard his child.
title: Ustaad Bhagat Singh

overview: A man returns to his country in order, ostensibly, to reform his girlfriend's violent family, but he seems to have a strange connection and a rather dark past.
title: Mirchi

overview: The film depicts the adolescent age of the Pandavas and Krishna and shows the events in the Mahabharata, focusing on the later chapters of Adi Parva and the first half of Sabha Parva.
title: Sri Krishna Pandaveeyam

overview: Madhava and Hema love each other but both suppress their feelings due to societal norms. When a horrific incident lands Hema in a mental asylum, Madhava risks everything to comes to her aid.
title: Aapadbandhavudu

overview: Shiva is a youngster searching for a job, and Sruthi is a software employee. Love blossoms into marriage for Siva and Sruthi, but Shiva's efforts at trying to find a job go unnoticed by Sruthi, which leads to complications in their relationship.
title: Kalyanam Kamaneeyam

overview: Vamsi falls in love with Bujji and pretends to be a CBI Officer to see her every day.
title: Ontari

overview: Achari America Yatra is a Telugu movie starring Vishnu Manchu and Brahmanandam Kanneganti in prominent roles. It is an action drama movie directed by G. Nageswara Reddy, with Darling Swamy as the writer, forming part of the crew.
title: Achari America Yatra

overview: The story is about a family in which mother and son together fight against father for the principles and human values. Srividhya, as a ditched wife, rises up her kid Rakesh (Venkatesh) with well behavior, manner and makes him a good lawyer to do justice to the fellow woman who are cheated brutally by their husbands. How Rakesh takes the revenge on his father for the injustice that he had done to his mother is the crux of the film.
title: Dharma Chakram

overview: Raja, a common man, and Rani, the daughter of a powerful minister, are brought together by the forest.
title: Bobbili Raja

overview: When asked by the king what his ambition is, prince Pratap says he wants to marry four celestial maidens. The angered king exiles him and Pratap sets off on a quest to find the maidens.
title: Jagadeka Veeruni Katha

overview: Amid a wave of killings, officer Kanchana uncovers activist Satyamurthy's dark truth-he exploits orphans for power and kills Bose to stay hidden. Kanchana exposes him, ending with a haunting reflection on betrayal and lost innocence.
title: Police Vari Heccharika

overview: Based on the life of the notorious thief Nageswara Rao, who was the most wanted thief of south India& managed to evade the authorities on several occasions in the 1970s, earning him the moniker of 'Tiger.'
title: Tiger Nageswara Rao

overview: Bhagya Lakshmi(Reshmi Menon) falls head over heels for Karthick(Rahul Ravindran). She tries hard and somehow wins over Karthick. When everything seems to be going fine between the couple, Karthick’s ex-lover, Vaishnavi(Jia) come into the scene and disrupts the love story. Why did Vaishnavi come back into Karthick’s life? What problems did she create for Karthick? and how does he come out of this mess? That forms the rest of the story.
title: Hyderabad Love Story

overview: Four friends gather to celebrate Halloween, and they begin reading an intriguing horror novel. Things take a strange turn as they begin to experience bizarre events while reading the book. Will they be able to escape the spirit that haunts them?
title: Boo

overview: It follows the story of four friends who face the wrath of a powerful man after their actions inadvertently result in a loss of face for him. They must now fight back against him for survival.
title: Evadu Thakkuva Kaadu

overview: When a charming NRI girl falls in love with a wealthy businessman, she unwittingly sparks conflict within his large joint family. How will her lover find a way to marry her, while still ensuring that his large family remains happy and harmonious?
title: Brahmotsavam

overview: Siddhartha, a typical young man, falls in love with Kokila. She too eventually falls for him and both get married. At first they live happily, however later on Siddhartha loses his eyes in an accident, which is when trouble starts for them.
title: Kokilam

overview: Eeshwar Chandra Prasad (Prabhas) is the son of Ram Murthy (Chalapathi Rao) and Shantamma (Sharada Urvashi). Ram Murthy wants his son to do some job. However, Shantamma pampers Eeshwar very much and hence he doesn't want to leave the village. Ram Murthy dies and in order to fulfil his last wish, Eeshwar goes to the city to earn money on the advice of his friend Basha (Ali), who was a pickpocket. Eeshwar could not meet Basha. On the other hand Kotaiah (Kota Srinivasa Rao) runs big land mafia in Hyderabad city and a bitter rival of Narsing Pahilwan (Pradeep Rawat). Saidulu (Subbaraju) is Narsing's brother. Once Saidulu hacks Kotaiah and his assistant, when Eeshwar accidentally saves him. Eeshwar gets a job in a tea stall run by Chandranna (Chandra Mohan). He earns good money and purchases two gold bangles for his mother and plans to leave the city.
title: Yogi

overview: Vishwanath is a millionaire who loves his daughter Anjali obsessively. When Vishwanath discovers that Anjali is in love with Rishi, a happy-go-lucky man from a middle class family, he tries his best to separate them.
title: Nuvve... Nuvve...

overview: A rural entertainer laced with action, drama.
title: Sivudu

overview: Ashok , a reliable high class pimp, sends his girl to Daniel on a fateful night, ignorant of the fact that the girl would be brutally murdered. Gowtham, a Small Resto owner meets Meena on the roadside, who was looking for a lift and she proposes to him in her first meeting.
title: Nireekshana

overview: A coming off age story set in the US
title: ViSa

overview: The story is set in the 1990s and follows the emotional and action-filled journey of Bachhala Malli, a rural hero. The narrative combines intense drama with romance, focusing on the protagonist’s challenges and personal growth in a rustic backdrop.
title: Bachhala Malli

overview: Gopi, a famous singer, falls in love with Vijaya, a petty thief. Things take a turn when he discovers that she is Dharma Rao's daughter, the man who was killed by his father.
title: Aatagadu

overview: Abhi, from his childhood, revels in the art of playing other people. His mother recognizes his extraordinary talent, propelling him into the world of acting. As he matures, he becomes a sought-after junior artist, always relegated to the background. The lines between reel and real life blur as Abhi faces a complex situation at home, with a supportive mother and a nagging and concerned father. A chance encounter with Likitha , the MD of a company, leads to love, and Abhi finds himself playing the role of a CEO. However, a conniving director presents an intriguing script, introducing Abhi to Nero, a self-absorbed and evil character with conquest on his mind.
title: Extra Ordinary Man
